rComments: Listen to all her advice, start the assignments early so you have time to think. She is excited about the course material, this helps with your interest level... the course material can be dull at times.

Very nice teacher. She isn't the most exciting, but she certainly enjoys what she does. Though this class was not the heaviest class you will see, it is hard to get an A+. Easy B with a bit of work, but anything over an A- is tough. Not really sure what I learned in it though...

she is an amazing prof. This course isn't very heavy for a 3rd year course: no midterms. Just a final, 1 project and 2 small assignments. Dr. Pick is willing to help you and she marks very fairly. There is no textbook, but her slides are enough to do well on the final!

This course is so boring. There's no midterm but there's a few assignments, a research paper and a final exam. The assignments are hard and there's no right/wrong answer and yet you always get a bad mark! She's very repetitive and doesn't put enough info on the slides. But she's a nice professor and is glad to help you when you need it!
